dct_description_sm: Sheets included NE sheet, NW sheet, SE sheet, SW sheet Glossy photograph on Kodak paper. Reproduction of a printed map. Reproduced by John Robbins, a former graduate student, in the Indiana University, Bloomington, Geography Dept. darkroom in about 1980. Shows townships, sections, drainage, roads, schools, post offices, quarries, and stone mills. Includes "Stone directory" listing quarries and the companies that operate them. 1 map on 4 sheets, photocopy.
Dimensions: 81 x 64 cm, on sheets 51 x 41 cm; Scale: Approximately 1:52,000
